ing market equilibrium, and covers the mechanics of matrices for solving larger equation systems. Furthermore, chapters dedicated to calculus, especially its applications in economics and the innovative use of infinitesimal methods, equip learners with tools to tackle profit maximization challenges, factor optimization, and beyond. Later chapters unfold the world of differential and difference equations, revealing their significance in analyzing dynamic systems. All these concepts are illuminated through practical examples and numerous images from economics and business, ensuring relevance and clarity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBusiness mathematics. 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh  amathematics, economics, business, computer science, calculus, infinitesimal methods, Difference Equations, factor optimization, profit maximization challenges, linear simultaneous equations.1 aWood, Justine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2023 Englishz978311131920908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2023z9783111318608oZDB-23-DMA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024z978311156434008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI and ITGP STEM IT PACKAGEz978311157407308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97816839293520 cprintz978168392937640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168392936940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781683929369423